hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Rate equations for $0<t<\tau$:
$$\frac{dN_S}{dt}=-\lambda_{n,S}N_S,\quad
\frac{dN_I}{dt}=\lambda_{n,S}N_S-(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)N_I,\quad
\frac{dN_P}{dt}=\lambda_{n,I}N_I.$$
2. Solve for $N_S(t)$:
$$N_S(t)=N_S(0)e^{-\lambda_{n,S}t}.$$
3. Define $\Delta=(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)-\lambda_{n,S}$.  The integrating factor for $N_I$ gives
$$\frac{d}{dt}\bigl(N_I e^{(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)t}\bigr)
=\lambda_{n,S}N_S(0)e^{-\lambda_{n,S}t}e^{(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)t}
=\lambda_{n,S}N_S(0)e^{\Delta t}.$$
Integrate from $0$ to $t$:
$$N_I(t)e^{(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)t}
=\lambda_{n,S}N_S(0)\frac{e^{\Delta t}-1}{\Delta},$$
so
$$N_I(t)=\frac{\lambda_{n,S}N_S(0)}{\Delta}
\bigl(e^{-\lambda_{n,S}t}-e^{-(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)t}\bigr).$$
4. Integrate for $N_P(\tau)$:
$$N_P(\tau)
=\int_0^\tau\lambda_{n,I}N_I(t')\,dt'
=\frac{\lambda_{n,I}\lambda_{n,S}N_S(0)}{\Delta}
\Bigl[\int_0^\tau e^{-\lambda_{n,S}t'}dt'
-\int_0^\tau e^{-(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)t'}dt'\Bigr].$$
Compute the integrals:
$$\int_0^\tau e^{-at}dt=\frac{1-e^{-a\tau}}{a}.$$
Hence
$$\frac{N_P(\tau)}{N_S(0)}
=\frac{\lambda_{n,I}\lambda_{n,S}}{\Delta}
\Bigl[\frac{1-e^{-\lambda_{n,S}\tau}}{\lambda_{n,S}}
-\frac{1-e^{-(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)\tau}}{\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta}\Bigr].$$
5. Simplify:
$$\frac{N_P(\tau)}{N_S(0)}
=\frac{\lambda_{n,I}}{\Delta}
\Bigl[1-e^{-\lambda_{n,S}\tau}
-\frac{\lambda_{n,S}}{\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta}
\bigl(1-e^{-(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)\tau}\bigr)\Bigr].$$
Noting $\Delta=(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)-\lambda_{n,S}$, one finds
$$\frac{N_P(\tau)}{N_S(0)}
=\frac{\lambda_{n,I}}{\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta}
-\frac{\lambda_{n,I}}{\Delta}e^{-\lambda_{n,S}\tau}
+\frac{\lambda_{n,I}\,\lambda_{n,S}}{(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)\,\Delta}
\,e^{-(\lambda_{n,I}+\lambda_\beta)\tau}.$$
After $t>\tau$, no further production occurs, so $N_P(\infty)=N_P(\tau)$.
